I'm Mark from Privacy

00:00:23.336 --> 00:00:24.736 A:middle
Engineering Team at Apple, and

00:00:24.736 --> 00:00:26.196 A:middle
with my colleague, Julien, we're

00:00:26.196 --> 00:00:27.926 A:middle
thrilled to tell you today about

00:00:27.926 --> 00:00:29.646 A:middle
designing for privacy on our

00:00:29.646 --> 00:00:31.366 A:middle
platforms and in your

00:00:31.366 --> 00:00:32.156 A:middle
applications.

00:00:34.096 --> 00:00:36.126 A:middle
Privacy isn't just about closing

00:00:36.126 --> 00:00:36.606 A:middle
doors.

00:00:37.226 --> 00:00:39.516 A:middle
It's also about opening doors to

00:00:39.516 --> 00:00:41.086 A:middle
the trust you build with your

00:00:41.126 --> 00:00:41.736 A:middle
customers.

00:00:43.516 --> 00:00:45.296 A:middle
Customers have let our devices

00:00:45.436 --> 00:00:48.586 A:middle
into their homes, captured the

00:00:48.586 --> 00:00:50.596 A:middle
memories in their photos,

00:00:52.326 --> 00:00:54.486 A:middle
monitor their health, and

00:00:54.686 --> 00:00:56.196 A:middle
transmit their thoughts and

00:00:56.196 --> 00:00:58.356 A:middle
emotions, knowing that they are

00:00:58.356 --> 00:00:59.726 A:middle
in control of their data.

00:01:02.436 --> 00:01:04.976 A:middle
As Tim said last year, we at

00:01:04.976 --> 00:01:07.526 A:middle
Apple can and do provide the

00:01:07.596 --> 00:01:09.876 A:middle
very best to our users while

00:01:09.876 --> 00:01:11.076 A:middle
treating their most precious

00:01:11.076 --> 00:01:12.776 A:middle
data like the precious cargo

00:01:12.986 --> 00:01:13.606 A:middle
that it is.

00:01:13.606 --> 00:01:17.066 A:middle
And if we can do it, then every

00:01:17.066 --> 00:01:19.206 A:middle
one of you can, and in today's

00:01:19.206 --> 00:01:21.746 A:middle
talk, we'll help you design for

00:01:21.746 --> 00:01:21.976 A:middle
privacy.

00:01:25.086 --> 00:01:28.406 A:middle
At Apple, privacy starts with

00:01:28.406 --> 00:01:29.526 A:middle
data minimization.

00:01:30.786 --> 00:01:32.756 A:middle
Examine carefully what data do

00:01:32.756 --> 00:01:34.066 A:middle
you need for the functionality

00:01:34.066 --> 00:01:35.806 A:middle
of your app, and what data can

00:01:35.806 --> 00:01:36.396 A:middle
you edit out?

00:01:39.426 --> 00:01:40.996 A:middle
Some of the most interesting and

00:01:40.996 --> 00:01:42.726 A:middle
challenging features use

00:01:42.726 --> 00:01:45.356 A:middle
sensitive, personal data, and at

00:01:45.356 --> 00:01:47.516 A:middle
Apple, we build these features

00:01:47.766 --> 00:01:50.126 A:middle
with on device intelligence, so

00:01:50.126 --> 00:01:52.396 A:middle
your device personalizes itself

00:01:52.566 --> 00:01:54.756 A:middle
to you, while Apple doesn't

00:01:54.756 --> 00:01:55.566 A:middle
collect this data.

00:01:58.506 --> 00:02:00.096 A:middle
When data is shared with Apple,

00:01:58.506 --> 00:02:00.096 A:middle
When data is shared with Apple,

00:02:00.336 --> 00:02:01.326 A:middle
we ask the customer.

00:02:02.446 --> 00:02:03.626 A:middle
The customer is always in

00:02:03.626 --> 00:02:05.766 A:middle
control, and they always know

00:02:06.076 --> 00:02:06.906 A:middle
what's being shared.

00:02:06.906 --> 00:02:11.706 A:middle
And security is foundational.

00:02:12.506 --> 00:02:13.946 A:middle
It not only protects people's

00:02:13.946 --> 00:02:16.166 A:middle
data on their devices and on our

00:02:16.166 --> 00:02:19.886 A:middle
servers but also enforces both

00:02:19.886 --> 00:02:21.356 A:middle
the privacy protections we've

00:02:21.406 --> 00:02:23.236 A:middle
built and the choices that

00:02:23.236 --> 00:02:26.836 A:middle
people have made.

00:02:26.836 --> 00:02:27.856 A:middle
Some companies think that

00:02:27.856 --> 00:02:30.766 A:middle
privacy is just security, that

00:02:30.766 --> 00:02:32.316 A:middle
you can use or collect data so

00:02:32.316 --> 00:02:33.026 A:middle
long as you protect it.

00:02:33.026 --> 00:02:35.956 A:middle
But that's short sighted, as

00:02:35.956 --> 00:02:37.866 A:middle
security alone isn't adequate in

00:02:37.866 --> 00:02:38.366 A:middle
the long run.

00:02:38.366 --> 00:02:41.556 A:middle
You do have a responsibility to

00:02:41.556 --> 00:02:42.416 A:middle
protect the data that you

00:02:42.416 --> 00:02:44.496 A:middle
collect, but it's less risky to

00:02:44.496 --> 00:02:45.866 A:middle
just not collect it in the first

00:02:45.866 --> 00:02:46.196 A:middle
place.

00:02:48.996 --> 00:02:50.236 A:middle
Some other companies define

00:02:50.236 --> 00:02:52.276 A:middle
privacy as just transparency and

00:02:52.276 --> 00:02:52.676 A:middle
control.

00:02:53.536 --> 00:02:55.026 A:middle
Let users know what you're doing

00:02:55.026 --> 00:02:56.616 A:middle
with their data, and let them

00:02:56.616 --> 00:02:58.216 A:middle
opt out if they don't like it.

00:02:59.586 --> 00:03:01.516 A:middle
But this is privacy after the

00:02:59.586 --> 00:03:01.516 A:middle
But this is privacy after the

00:03:01.516 --> 00:03:04.646 A:middle
fact, and it forces people to

00:03:04.646 --> 00:03:06.676 A:middle
choose between privacy and

00:03:06.746 --> 00:03:07.286 A:middle
features.

00:03:07.336 --> 00:03:09.926 A:middle
And the burden shouldn't be on

00:03:09.926 --> 00:03:12.266 A:middle
individuals to exercise control

00:03:12.556 --> 00:03:13.556 A:middle
to get privacy.

00:03:15.676 --> 00:03:17.176 A:middle
Because privacy is a fundamental

00:03:17.176 --> 00:03:17.756 A:middle
human right.

00:03:17.756 --> 00:03:20.036 A:middle
It's essential to the

00:03:20.036 --> 00:03:21.666 A:middle
functioning of good societies,

00:03:21.946 --> 00:03:24.536 A:middle
and it's too important to not

00:03:24.536 --> 00:03:26.486 A:middle
just work in the technologies

00:03:26.486 --> 00:03:27.206 A:middle
that we use.

00:03:27.366 --> 00:03:30.626 A:middle
That's why at Apple, privacy is

00:03:30.626 --> 00:03:32.376 A:middle
designed into our futures.

00:03:33.066 --> 00:03:34.526 A:middle
It's [inaudible] how they work,

00:03:35.186 --> 00:03:36.666 A:middle
not something added on at the

00:03:36.666 --> 00:03:36.956 A:middle
end.

00:03:37.076 --> 00:03:40.306 A:middle
At Apple, we challenge ourselves

00:03:40.376 --> 00:03:42.026 A:middle
every day to build great

00:03:42.026 --> 00:03:44.226 A:middle
features with privacy, and we're

00:03:44.226 --> 00:03:47.436 A:middle
confident you can too.

00:03:48.026 --> 00:03:50.296 A:middle
In the rest of our talk, we'll

00:03:50.296 --> 00:03:51.876 A:middle
explore privacy and the user

00:03:51.876 --> 00:03:52.526 A:middle
experience.

00:03:53.406 --> 00:03:55.416 A:middle
Dive into what's new and updated

00:03:55.416 --> 00:03:57.566 A:middle
in frameworks, and then we'll

00:03:57.566 --> 00:03:59.426 A:middle
take a step back and show how

00:03:59.426 --> 00:04:00.806 A:middle
you can overcome privacy

00:03:59.426 --> 00:04:00.806 A:middle
you can overcome privacy

00:04:00.806 --> 00:04:02.396 A:middle
challenges through innovation.

00:04:04.556 --> 00:04:06.046 A:middle
I'm going to talk about four

00:04:06.046 --> 00:04:07.176 A:middle
user experiences today.

00:04:09.456 --> 00:04:12.136 A:middle
First, Sign In with Apple, which

00:04:12.136 --> 00:04:12.956 A:middle
allows you to connect your

00:04:12.956 --> 00:04:14.586 A:middle
user's experience across

00:04:14.656 --> 00:04:16.426 A:middle
platforms without having to

00:04:16.426 --> 00:04:17.606 A:middle
store or manage user

00:04:17.606 --> 00:04:20.745 A:middle
credentials, and it's a great

00:04:20.745 --> 00:04:22.366 A:middle
example of data minimization.

00:04:22.866 --> 00:04:25.206 A:middle
Apple doesn't track how people

00:04:25.206 --> 00:04:27.266 A:middle
use your application because

00:04:27.266 --> 00:04:29.506 A:middle
it's none of our business, and

00:04:29.836 --> 00:04:31.146 A:middle
we've pared down the data that

00:04:31.146 --> 00:04:32.246 A:middle
people share through Sign In

00:04:32.246 --> 00:04:34.036 A:middle
with Apple to just what's needed

00:04:34.036 --> 00:04:35.316 A:middle
to sign into your application.

00:04:36.546 --> 00:04:37.786 A:middle
So, ask yourself if you really

00:04:37.786 --> 00:04:39.106 A:middle
need the customer's name or

00:04:39.106 --> 00:04:39.876 A:middle
email address.

00:04:40.736 --> 00:04:42.886 A:middle
If you need a name for billing

00:04:42.886 --> 00:04:44.236 A:middle
or shipping purposes, you can

00:04:44.236 --> 00:04:45.506 A:middle
get it later, for example,

00:04:45.686 --> 00:04:46.346 A:middle
through Apple Pay.

00:04:46.346 --> 00:04:49.226 A:middle
And if you don't ask for any

00:04:49.226 --> 00:04:50.996 A:middle
additional data, the user has

00:04:50.996 --> 00:04:53.046 A:middle
just one button to tap, and

00:04:53.046 --> 00:04:53.706 A:middle
they're signed into your

00:04:53.706 --> 00:04:54.206 A:middle
application.

00:04:55.686 --> 00:04:57.766 A:middle
If you do need to contact the

00:04:57.766 --> 00:04:59.316 A:middle
user, for example, to provide

00:04:59.316 --> 00:05:00.536 A:middle
receipts or for account

00:04:59.316 --> 00:05:00.536 A:middle
receipts or for account

00:05:00.536 --> 00:05:02.916 A:middle
recovery, we provide an easy way

00:05:02.916 --> 00:05:03.586 A:middle
for you to do so.

00:05:04.276 --> 00:05:07.196 A:middle
People can be hesitant to share

00:05:07.196 --> 00:05:08.336 A:middle
their real email address.

00:05:08.926 --> 00:05:09.936 A:middle
We've all seen email lists

00:05:10.006 --> 00:05:13.686 A:middle
stolen or resold and then abused

00:05:13.686 --> 00:05:14.416 A:middle
by spammers.

00:05:15.136 --> 00:05:16.526 A:middle
So people may give you a fake

00:05:16.526 --> 00:05:18.286 A:middle
email address or one for an

00:05:18.286 --> 00:05:20.396 A:middle
account they never check.

00:05:20.616 --> 00:05:21.996 A:middle
You could make the user verify

00:05:21.996 --> 00:05:23.616 A:middle
their email at sign-in, but this

00:05:23.646 --> 00:05:24.536 A:middle
takes them out of your

00:05:24.536 --> 00:05:26.556 A:middle
application, potentially to

00:05:26.556 --> 00:05:27.306 A:middle
[inaudible] their spam folder,

00:05:27.306 --> 00:05:28.756 A:middle
and that's not a great

00:05:28.756 --> 00:05:29.386 A:middle
experience.

00:05:30.436 --> 00:05:31.796 A:middle
With sign-in with Apple, you

00:05:31.796 --> 00:05:33.526 A:middle
will get a verified email

00:05:33.526 --> 00:05:35.526 A:middle
address associated with the

00:05:35.526 --> 00:05:36.386 A:middle
user's AppleID.

00:05:37.856 --> 00:05:40.036 A:middle
Customers can choose to hide

00:05:40.036 --> 00:05:41.676 A:middle
their email address, in which

00:05:41.676 --> 00:05:43.056 A:middle
case you'll get an address

00:05:43.206 --> 00:05:45.106 A:middle
managed by Apple through which

00:05:45.106 --> 00:05:46.756 A:middle
we relay your emails to the

00:05:46.756 --> 00:05:48.176 A:middle
customer and vice versa.

00:05:48.476 --> 00:05:50.526 A:middle
And Apple won't retain emails

00:05:50.606 --> 00:05:52.436 A:middle
after we've delivered them.

00:05:53.066 --> 00:05:54.636 A:middle
For each customer, this managed

00:05:54.636 --> 00:05:56.036 A:middle
address is different for each

00:05:56.036 --> 00:05:58.316 A:middle
developer, so customers are in

00:05:58.316 --> 00:06:00.116 A:middle
control of which developers they

00:05:58.316 --> 00:06:00.116 A:middle
control of which developers they

00:06:00.116 --> 00:06:02.286 A:middle
want to receive email from, and

00:06:02.286 --> 00:06:03.866 A:middle
you're in control of who can

00:06:03.866 --> 00:06:05.096 A:middle
send emails to the managed

00:06:05.096 --> 00:06:06.906 A:middle
address we provide you, since

00:06:06.906 --> 00:06:08.266 A:middle
you can whitelist domains or

00:06:08.266 --> 00:06:09.836 A:middle
addresses that we'll accept

00:06:09.836 --> 00:06:10.716 A:middle
incoming mail from.

00:06:10.886 --> 00:06:12.946 A:middle
And because both parties are in

00:06:12.946 --> 00:06:14.596 A:middle
control, we think this is your

00:06:14.636 --> 00:06:16.536 A:middle
best shot at getting your emails

00:06:16.536 --> 00:06:17.726 A:middle
in front of your customer.

00:06:20.676 --> 00:06:22.306 A:middle
We understand you face

00:06:22.306 --> 00:06:23.966 A:middle
challenges in preventing abuse

00:06:24.026 --> 00:06:25.386 A:middle
and fraud from account farming.

00:06:25.386 --> 00:06:27.966 A:middle
And you may want to ask users to

00:06:27.966 --> 00:06:29.336 A:middle
fill out a CAPTCHA such as this.

00:06:29.946 --> 00:06:31.466 A:middle
But these are cumbersome, and

00:06:31.466 --> 00:06:32.676 A:middle
they're difficult to localize

00:06:32.676 --> 00:06:35.796 A:middle
and make accessible.

00:06:35.796 --> 00:06:37.216 A:middle
Other alternatives are invasive

00:06:37.216 --> 00:06:39.316 A:middle
to user's privacy, such as

00:06:39.366 --> 00:06:40.716 A:middle
trying to reidentify them with

00:06:40.716 --> 00:06:41.716 A:middle
personally identifiable

00:06:41.716 --> 00:06:43.496 A:middle
information or fingerprinting.

00:06:43.496 --> 00:06:46.436 A:middle
With Sign In with Apple, we can

00:06:46.516 --> 00:06:48.956 A:middle
leverage on-device intelligence

00:06:49.326 --> 00:06:51.466 A:middle
to provide you with one bit that

00:06:51.466 --> 00:06:53.126 A:middle
indicates a user is likely real.

00:06:53.126 --> 00:06:56.016 A:middle
And this flag is supported on

00:06:56.016 --> 00:06:57.626 A:middle
iOS, and we provide it at

00:06:57.626 --> 00:06:58.426 A:middle
account creation.

00:07:01.436 --> 00:07:03.296 A:middle
The real user status property of

00:07:03.296 --> 00:07:05.336 A:middle
ASAuthorizationAppleIDCredential

00:07:05.656 --> 00:07:06.776 A:middle
is how you check for this bit.

00:07:06.876 --> 00:07:09.546 A:middle
And keep in mind that a new user

00:07:09.716 --> 00:07:11.596 A:middle
on a new phone will likely show

00:07:11.596 --> 00:07:13.326 A:middle
up as status unknown, so you

00:07:13.326 --> 00:07:14.676 A:middle
shouldn't just deny service if

00:07:14.676 --> 00:07:16.386 A:middle
you see this state and provide

00:07:16.386 --> 00:07:17.796 A:middle
the user and ultimate flow or a

00:07:18.136 --> 00:07:19.236 A:middle
way to appeal this

00:07:19.236 --> 00:07:19.756 A:middle
determination.

00:07:19.756 --> 00:07:23.516 A:middle
So that was Sign In with Apple,

00:07:23.666 --> 00:07:25.576 A:middle
a great privacy friendly single

00:07:25.576 --> 00:07:26.346 A:middle
sign on solution.

00:07:28.216 --> 00:07:29.356 A:middle
Now, let's talk about location.

00:07:30.486 --> 00:07:32.046 A:middle
People are protective of where

00:07:32.046 --> 00:07:33.606 A:middle
they are and where they've been.

00:07:33.746 --> 00:07:38.126 A:middle
It reveals where we live, places

00:07:38.126 --> 00:07:40.116 A:middle
we frequent, our patterns of

00:07:40.116 --> 00:07:41.466 A:middle
life, and when those patterns

00:07:41.466 --> 00:07:42.056 A:middle
change.

00:07:42.956 --> 00:07:44.186 A:middle
Like if you start attending a

00:07:44.186 --> 00:07:45.436 A:middle
different set of afterparties

00:07:45.436 --> 00:07:46.756 A:middle
this year with a different crowd

00:07:46.756 --> 00:07:47.076 A:middle
of people.

00:07:47.076 --> 00:07:49.836 A:middle
And in iOS 13, we're making

00:07:49.836 --> 00:07:51.836 A:middle
changes to help users exercise

00:07:52.066 --> 00:07:53.986 A:middle
smarter control over when

00:07:53.986 --> 00:07:55.056 A:middle
they're sharing their location.

00:07:57.206 --> 00:07:58.796 A:middle
Previously in iOS, there was a

00:07:58.856 --> 00:08:00.576 A:middle
one-time prompt for location

00:07:58.856 --> 00:08:00.576 A:middle
one-time prompt for location

00:08:00.576 --> 00:08:03.646 A:middle
permissions, and at this point,

00:08:03.646 --> 00:08:04.876 A:middle
the user hasn't experienced

00:08:04.876 --> 00:08:07.386 A:middle
location in your app before.

00:08:07.446 --> 00:08:08.936 A:middle
So they may select don't allow

00:08:08.966 --> 00:08:10.696 A:middle
and miss out on the value that

00:08:10.696 --> 00:08:11.996 A:middle
location can provide in your

00:08:11.996 --> 00:08:12.546 A:middle
application.

00:08:12.636 --> 00:08:14.976 A:middle
And while many of you have built

00:08:14.976 --> 00:08:16.706 A:middle
experiences to explain your use

00:08:16.706 --> 00:08:18.276 A:middle
of location before asking,

00:08:19.056 --> 00:08:20.206 A:middle
nothing explains better than

00:08:20.206 --> 00:08:20.916 A:middle
using your app.

00:08:22.106 --> 00:08:23.956 A:middle
So, in iOS 13 were introducing a

00:08:23.956 --> 00:08:27.686 A:middle
new option, Allow Once, giving

00:08:27.686 --> 00:08:29.916 A:middle
users the ability to try out

00:08:29.916 --> 00:08:31.336 A:middle
location in your application

00:08:31.766 --> 00:08:33.176 A:middle
before committing to a decision.

00:08:33.635 --> 00:08:36.446 A:middle
If the user selects Allow Once,

00:08:36.946 --> 00:08:38.056 A:middle
your app will have access to

00:08:38.056 --> 00:08:39.566 A:middle
location, just as if the user

00:08:39.566 --> 00:08:42.126 A:middle
had selected While in Use up

00:08:42.126 --> 00:08:43.515 A:middle
until the system no longer

00:08:43.515 --> 00:08:45.116 A:middle
considers your app in use.

00:08:45.596 --> 00:08:46.766 A:middle
The next time the user launches

00:08:46.766 --> 00:08:47.786 A:middle
your app, they'll be asked

00:08:47.786 --> 00:08:49.816 A:middle
again, and if they want to give

00:08:49.816 --> 00:08:51.026 A:middle
you app access without being

00:08:51.026 --> 00:08:52.476 A:middle
asked, they can grant While in

00:08:52.476 --> 00:08:53.736 A:middle
Use when they're comfortable

00:08:53.736 --> 00:08:54.196 A:middle
doing so.

00:08:55.766 --> 00:08:56.666 A:middle
What about Always?

00:08:57.576 --> 00:08:58.756 A:middle
The ability to access a user's

00:08:58.756 --> 00:09:00.296 A:middle
location always is a very

00:08:58.756 --> 00:09:00.296 A:middle
location always is a very

00:09:00.296 --> 00:09:02.246 A:middle
powerful capability, and you

00:09:02.246 --> 00:09:03.776 A:middle
just may be surprised if your

00:09:03.776 --> 00:09:05.396 A:middle
app asks for it right away

00:09:05.916 --> 00:09:06.836 A:middle
before you've had a chance to

00:09:06.836 --> 00:09:08.086 A:middle
demonstrate your app's value,

00:09:09.046 --> 00:09:10.106 A:middle
the value of location in your

00:09:10.106 --> 00:09:11.816 A:middle
app's value, or why you need it

00:09:11.816 --> 00:09:12.956 A:middle
in the background when they're

00:09:12.996 --> 00:09:15.736 A:middle
currently using your app.

00:09:15.936 --> 00:09:18.326 A:middle
Location prompts in app will now

00:09:18.366 --> 00:09:21.086 A:middle
always be for just once or While

00:09:21.086 --> 00:09:21.526 A:middle
in Use.

00:09:22.196 --> 00:09:25.536 A:middle
If you do request Always, we'll

